Generators
__________

--> this generator is special function that returns the iterator.
    instead of returning all the valus at once...

--> here we are going to use yield keyword

eg :
def some():
    yield 1
    yield 2
    yield 3
so=some()
print(next(so))
print(next(so))
print(next(so))

working a generator
_______ _ _________

--> it does not execute the function immediately. .
--> it will returns the generator object.
--> then the function will pauses at each yield.
--> when the next() is called again , execution resumes from where it stopped .


def demo():
    print("start")
    yield 1

    print("middle")
    yield 2

    print("end")
    yield 3
how=demo()
print(next(how))

