function
________

--> return
--> return complete result.
--> function will end after the return the value.
--> more memory usage.
--> this function never resume.

generator
_________

--> yield
--> return one value every yield.
--> pauses after every yield.
--> less memory usage.
--> resume after next().

yield keyword
_____ _______

--> this will produce the value..
--> but the yield pauses the funtion.
--> and yield will save the function current state.
--> yiels will continues where it stopped.



next() keyword
_____ ________

--> the next() function is used to retrive the next value from a generator.

StopIteration
_____________

--> calling next() function after all values retrive then it will raise the
StopIteration exception.

eg:
def how(so):
    for i in range (so):
       yield i*i
any=how(5)
print(next(any))
print(next(any))
print(next(any))
print(next(any))
print(next(any))
print(next(any))


def num(a):
    for i in range(a,0,-2):
        yield i

any=num(10)
print(next(any))
print(next(any))

